Sentencas: The defect structure model of La0.5Ba0.5CoO3-delta was successfully verified using a combined set of coulometric and thermogravimetric data.
Titulo: Defect-Induced Properties and Thermodynamics of La0.5Ba0.5CoO3-δ

Sentencas: The results were used to model the dependences of Seebeck coefficient, measured vs T and pO(2) simultaneously with the total conductivity, and chemical strain of this oxide.
Titulo: Defect-Induced Properties and Thermodynamics of La0.5Ba0.5CoO3-δ

Sentencas: The partial molar enthalpy of oxygen in La0.5Ba0.5CoO3-delta was calculated from the defect structure model and used to evaluate the enthalpy increments and high-temperature heat capacity of an oxide with constant chemical composition, La0.5Ba0.5CoO2.99, from the drop calorimetric measurement results in air.
Titulo: Defect-Induced Properties and Thermodynamics of La0.5Ba0.5CoO3-δ

Sentencas: The standard enthalpies of formation of cubic La0.5Ba0.5CoO2.95 and double LaBaCo2O5.90 perovskites, and the enthalpy of cation ordering in A-sublattice of La0.5Ba0.5CoO2.95, were found using the results of solution calorimetry at 298.15 K.
Titulo: Defect-Induced Properties and Thermodynamics of La0.5Ba0.5CoO3-δ

Sentencas: With the data obtained, we predicted the chemical compatibility of La0.5Ba0.5CoO3-delta with solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) electrolyte materials.
Titulo: Defect-Induced Properties and Thermodynamics of La0.5Ba0.5CoO3-δ
